# ================================
# HOW MULTIPLE USERS WORK
# ================================
# 
# You (Developer):
# - Register ONE app with Tradovate â†’ Get client_id + client_secret
# - Set the credentials above
# 
# Your Users (Alice, Bob, Carol, etc.):
# - Each has their OWN Tradovate account
# - Each authenticates through YOUR registered app
# - Each gets their OWN unique access token
# - Tokens are stored separately per user
# 
# Example Token Storage:
# - localStorage.tradovate_demo_token_alice = "token123"
# - localStorage.tradovate_demo_token_bob = "token456"  
# - localStorage.tradovate_demo_token_carol = "token789"
#
# Security:
# - Alice only sees Alice's trading data
# - Bob only sees Bob's trading data
# - Carol only sees Carol's trading data
# - Your app uses the same client_id for all OAuth requests
# - But each user gets isolated access to their own account

